article.headline: Wagner 82, Maryland-Eastern Shore 76
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Mark Porter had 21 points, nine rebounds and six assists to lead Wagner past Maryland-Eastern Shore 82-76 on Saturday. James Ulrich added 18 points and 14 rebounds for the Seahawks (1-2), who had five players score in double figures. Corey Brown scored 23 points, including 18 in the first half, to lead the Hawks (0-1). Jesse Brooks had 20, and Antonio McMillion and Ed Tyson each scored 14. UMES led 36-34 at halftime and extended its advantage to 43-36 early in the second half, but Wagner responded with a 14-1 run to take a 50-44 lead with 14 minutes to play. The Hawks got no closer than four points the rest of the way, and the Seahawks led by 14 with 1:30 remaining. The Seahawks shot 55 percent (16-for-29) from the floor in the second half. Joey Mundweiler went 4-for-7 from 3-point range and scored 14 points. Jamal Smith also scored 14, and Justin Drummond had 10.
